            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-21 11:50:20" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a relatively small and often temporary type of object on which a person may lie or recline; made of reeds or cloth; thin and light for carrying</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>cot</Gloss>
                <Gloss>pallet</Gloss>
                <Gloss>stretcher</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of contexts the terms κλινίδιον, κλινάριον, and κράβαττος refer to cots or stretchers on which sick or convalescent persons might be resting or on which they could be transported. There is no NT context in which these terms refer to couches on which people reclined while eating.</Comments>
